Great.

29:33.040 --> 29:34.000
Great.

29:53.480 --> 29:54.480
What happened?

29:59.160 --> 30:00.160
Isn't it obvious?

30:01.400 --> 30:02.480
No, it's not.

30:05.800 --> 30:07.760
Why did you do it?
This isn't you.

30:13.640 --> 30:16.800
My job is to interrogate,
so you'd better start talking

30:16.960 --> 30:18.080
and get this over with.

30:19.840 --> 30:20.840
Sol.

30:24.080 --> 30:25.560
They were talking about you.

30:27.160 --> 30:28.320
You got in a fight over me?

30:34.880 --> 30:35.880
I'm sorry.

30:38.240 --> 30:39.760
I'm sorry you're having...

30:41.120 --> 30:43.440
to go through all this
because of me, really.

30:48.720 --> 30:51.080
I want to go live
with Grandma for a while.

30:52.840 --> 30:53.840
What?

30:55.160 --> 30:57.120
-I'm going to live with Grandma.
-No.

31:01.000 --> 31:02.720
Look, Sol, I know I haven't...

31:03.760 --> 31:05.000
been the best mom.

31:06.160 --> 31:08.560
I made mistakes,
I wasn't what you deserve...

31:10.040 --> 31:11.440
Maybe I haven't been the mom

31:12.600 --> 31:14.480
you would have wanted, but I...

31:19.960 --> 31:21.520
We've always been together.

31:24.120 --> 31:26.200
You're the best thing
in my life.

31:29.040 --> 31:30.520
Sol, look at me.

31:31.800 --> 31:32.800
Please.

31:35.960 --> 31:39.160
-I want to live with Grandma.
-Okay.

31:47.240 --> 31:48.280
This is like Paradise.

31:49.040 --> 31:51.080
If this were mine,
I'd never leave.

31:51.240 --> 31:52.520
I'm glad to hear it.

31:53.320 --> 31:56.040
-You'll be here a lot.
-As long as you need.

31:56.680 --> 31:59.400
So... about the contract,
what were you thinking?

32:00.400 --> 32:02.320
I'd like it all
to be above board,

32:02.440 --> 32:05.080
I need to start paying
my social security.

32:05.240 --> 32:07.880
But if you weren't thinking
along those lines...

32:08.000 --> 32:09.160
Whoa!

32:09.360 --> 32:11.120
A tennis court.

32:12.080 --> 32:14.400
If you like, I can help you
clean it up a bit.

32:14.520 --> 32:15.920
That won't be necessary.

32:16.160 --> 32:19.920
So, what will be
my job here exactly?

32:21.000 --> 32:23.080
-We're nearly there.
-Excuse my eagerness.

32:23.240 --> 32:25.360
When you live outside
of the general population

32:25.520 --> 32:28.640
-and have a chance to...
-Society is harsh...

32:29.480 --> 32:31.120
You don't know
how thankful I am.

32:31.280 --> 32:34.120
Down-to-earth people like you
just don't exist anymore.

32:35.120 --> 32:38.840
You live in a mansion, I live
in a windowless cardboard box,

32:39.440 --> 32:40.480
and even so...

32:43.200 --> 32:45.400
Turn around,
you'll see a lemon tree.

32:46.640 --> 32:48.280
A lemon tree? No. Where...?

33:23.080 --> 33:24.160
Isabel.

33:26.200 --> 33:27.200
-Am I alright?
-Yes.

33:31.360 --> 33:32.480
Isabel, excuse me.

33:33.000 --> 33:35.120
A quick question, Isabel.
Just one.

33:36.560 --> 33:38.360
You must have something to say.

33:39.640 --> 33:42.080
-Just give us something.
-No, don't close it.

33:42.600 --> 33:45.080
Just a moment.
Hang on, just one question.

33:49.560 --> 33:51.040
I do want to say something.

33:58.160 --> 33:59.640
About the lack of integrity

34:00.400 --> 34:02.080
and shameless actions

34:02.080 --> 34:02.120
and shameless actions
of certain so-called
journalistic professionals,

34:02.120 --> 34:05.640
of certain so-called
journalistic professionals,

34:05.800 --> 34:08.080
who couldn't care less
about the consequences

34:08.200 --> 34:10.280
or suffering caused
by their actions.

34:10.400 --> 34:12.240
And claiming as justification,

34:13.080 --> 34:15.960
the right to information,

34:16.120 --> 34:19.160
they're capable of stooping
to the lowest of the low,

34:19.280 --> 34:22.040
-because they're vultures.
-Is this aimed at me?

34:22.040 --> 34:22.120
-because they're vultures.
-Is this aimed at me?
What kind of journalism
rips families apart?

34:22.120 --> 34:25.160
What kind of journalism
rips families apart?

34:25.760 --> 34:27.200
Destroys people.

34:27.400 --> 34:29.440
So, you don't believe
in freedom of the press?

34:29.560 --> 34:32.320
-No.
-Do you want censoring?

34:32.520 --> 34:35.000
-No.
-Who decides what's relevant?

34:35.160 --> 34:38.040
This is from a representative
of the Police Force.

34:38.040 --> 34:39.040
PROTECTION

34:45.040 --> 34:48.000
What's going on there?
What the hell is Isabel doing?

34:48.120 --> 34:49.120
Wait here.

34:51.080 --> 34:54.960
If you let me speak,
all I'm asking for is respect

34:55.120 --> 34:56.240
and a right to privacy.

34:57.000 --> 34:58.640
We're talking
about a murderer.

34:58.800 --> 35:02.320
Shouldn't privacy come second
when people are dying?

35:02.520 --> 35:03.960
I'd remind you
the Constitution...

35:04.080 --> 35:06.120
What's the Constitution
got to do with the fact

35:06.280 --> 35:09.280
that you reported
I'd been raped as a minor?

35:09.480 --> 35:10.640
What does it...

35:11.000 --> 35:13.160
Why didn't you tell me
about your daughter?

35:14.160 --> 35:16.400
Because you were the patient,
not me.

35:16.600 --> 35:19.000
-What's it got to do with that?
-Thank you.

35:19.200 --> 35:21.080
That's enough for today, thanks.

35:21.080 --> 35:23.440
If we find anything,
you'll be the first to know.

35:25.680 --> 35:27.480
That's the worst thing
you could do.

35:29.920 --> 35:30.920
Nailed it.

35:34.160 --> 35:35.160
What a moment.

35:41.200 --> 35:43.000
-Where are you going?
-To demand protection.

35:43.120 --> 35:45.360
It's my duty, don't you think?

35:45.520 --> 35:46.520
No.

35:47.120 --> 35:49.560
I don't have to do
everything you ask.

35:49.720 --> 35:51.960
Someone who is unstable
needs a guide.

35:52.080 --> 35:53.200
Is that right?

35:53.360 --> 35:56.920
You think I'm just some loser
who's worthless on his own.

35:58.160 --> 35:59.360
No, it's not that.

36:03.040 --> 36:04.760
I don't want you to get hurt.

36:07.000 --> 36:08.000
But I will.

36:09.800 --> 36:12.560
Do what I tell you
and you'll be fine.

36:45.640 --> 36:46.600
Help me!

36:48.080 --> 36:50.560
Can anyone hear me?
Get me out of here, please!

37:05.040 --> 37:07.120
Your life will finally
have meaning.

37:15.040 --> 37:16.800
-Let me help.
-I've got it.

37:21.320 --> 37:22.560
I'll go get the rest.

37:24.360 --> 37:26.080
Don't worry,
it's only temporary.

37:29.000 --> 37:30.320
She's taking
her snorkeling gear.

37:30.440 --> 37:31.760
She won't even look at me.

37:32.400 --> 37:34.600
And you won't look at me...

37:34.800 --> 37:36.600
It's a good thing
there are only three of us.

37:36.720 --> 37:38.120
It must be hereditary.

37:39.160 --> 37:42.080
Everyone needs a breather,
and space sometime.

37:42.840 --> 37:44.240
I'm the only one who
wants to see you both.

37:44.440 --> 37:45.680
I could say no, I'm her mom.

37:47.200 --> 37:50.000
I can tell you from experience
that doesn't work.

37:52.440 --> 37:54.360
I want to know
her comings and goings,

37:54.520 --> 37:57.920
-what she eats and doesn't.
-What about you?

37:59.080 --> 38:01.920
-Who updates me on you?
-I can look after myself.

38:03.600 --> 38:07.160
You be careful. Your friend
lives in a rough area.

38:07.480 --> 38:09.720
-What friend?
-The one from the hostel.

38:10.360 --> 38:14.080
-Don't worry about me.
-What if you get robbed or hurt.

38:14.280 --> 38:17.000
You can leave the fish.
I think I can keep him alive.

38:17.160 --> 38:20.040
I doubt it, Mom.
You always forget to feed him.

38:32.560 --> 38:33.560
In you get.

38:34.120 --> 38:35.120
-Bye.
-Bye.

39:03.560 --> 39:05.440
Shame, they're leaving
you alone, Isabel.

39:14.000 --> 39:15.040
What a circus.

39:17.440 --> 39:19.640
They're in there
on hunger strike.

39:22.040 --> 39:25.160
And they won't come out
until you find the killer.

39:25.680 --> 39:27.560
Or until nature takes
its course.

39:29.680 --> 39:32.440
I don't want another two deaths
on my conscience.

39:37.000 --> 39:40.360
JUSTICE
WE WANT PROTECTION

39:40.520 --> 39:42.560
-Thanks.
-Thanks.

39:43.880 --> 39:46.800
-This will do for a while.
-Yeah.

39:47.120 --> 39:49.800
Hey, how long can a person
last without food?

39:50.240 --> 39:52.000
Some, up to 73 days.

39:53.400 --> 39:55.920
I need a new wardrobe.
Something less perky.

39:57.600 --> 39:59.320
This report is so important,
Javi.

39:59.480 --> 40:02.040
-You get it, right?
-Then, are we with

40:02.200 --> 40:05.480
-these guys or the others.
-With whoever we need.

40:10.240 --> 40:13.840
Alright, I'm going home.
Call me with anything.

40:14.000 --> 40:15.120
Whatever time it is.

40:16.320 --> 40:17.800
You coming for dinner?

40:18.480 --> 40:19.800
Me, you and your wife?

40:20.640 --> 40:22.040
Threesomes aren't my thing.

40:23.160 --> 40:24.520
I thought you were modern.

40:30.400 --> 40:35.040
Javi, call my husband,
tell him I got caught up here.

40:36.000 --> 40:37.040
Right.

40:49.520 --> 40:51.080
Alright, rest up.

40:56.880 --> 40:57.880
I'm all done.

40:59.360 --> 41:01.840
Shall we head to your place
and unwind?

41:02.600 --> 41:03.640
I don't think so.

41:05.440 --> 41:06.440
Right.

41:07.440 --> 41:08.440
Okay, then.

41:09.040 --> 41:11.440
Next time you call,
I might be busy.

41:13.440 --> 41:14.520
I'll take the risk.

41:17.720 --> 41:18.720
Goodnight.

41:53.240 --> 41:54.240
Sol.

41:57.320 --> 42:00.240
That's the reaction you want
when visiting someone.

42:01.160 --> 42:04.840
-I thought you were my daughter.
-What, is she out past curfew?

42:05.040 --> 42:07.000
No. She's gone to
live with my mother.

42:09.760 --> 42:10.840
So, what is it?

42:17.120 --> 42:19.240
I've arranged
for your car to be rescued.

42:21.680 --> 42:22.920
You didn't have to.

42:24.680 --> 42:25.760
I didn't have to.

42:26.560 --> 42:28.480
-But I did.
-Thanks.

42:29.160 --> 42:31.240
Didn't they think it was odd,

42:31.360 --> 42:33.080
a police officer's car
in a lake?

42:33.080 --> 42:33.120
a police officer's car
in a lake?
-They didn't ask?
-It's all settled.

42:33.120 --> 42:34.760
-They didn't ask?
-It's all settled.

42:34.920 --> 42:35.920
Okay.

42:37.160 --> 42:39.120
Right. That was all.

42:39.800 --> 42:40.800
Bye.

42:41.360 --> 42:42.360
Want some soup?

42:44.560 --> 42:45.560
-Soup?
-Yes.

42:46.720 --> 42:48.880
I was going to open a can and...

42:49.000 --> 42:51.120
I don't want
to throw out the rest.

42:52.640 --> 42:54.040
Well... that seems like

42:54.240 --> 42:56.920
-a good enough reason.
-Let me open it.

42:58.720 --> 42:59.720
They're the same.

43:03.320 --> 43:06.960
Minestrone, I don't know if
it's any good, it might be crap.

43:38.120 --> 43:40.160
I hope you won't shoot me
this time.

43:42.080 --> 43:43.080
No.

44:55.680 --> 44:57.120
You can't be happy.

